{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-a46f97c5451374e1", "type": "tool_result", "content": "=== arxiv (5 results) ===\n  1. Towards a Phonology-Informed Evaluation of Multilingual TTS\n     https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.01965\n     [authors=Sneha Ray Barman, Neeraj Kumar Sharma, Shakuntala Mahanta | published=2026-07-02 | primary_category=cs.CL | id=2607.01965]\n  2. Improve Bilingual TTS Using Dynamic Language and Phonology Embedding\n     https://arxiv.org/abs/2212.03435\n     [authors=Fengyu Yang, Jian Luan, Yujun Wang | published=2022-12-07 | primary_category=cs.SD | id=2212.03435]\n  3. Phonology\n     https://arxiv.org/abs/cs/0204025\n     [authors=Steven Bird | published=2002-04-11 | primary_category=cs.CL | id=cs/0204025]\n  4. Probing the phonetic and phonological knowledge of tones in Mandarin TTS models\n     https://arxiv.org/abs/1912.10915\n     [authors=Jian Zhu | published=2019-12-23 | primary_category=cs.CL | id=1912.10915]\n  5. A lexical database tool for quantitative phonological research\n     https://arxiv.org/abs/cmp-lg/9707011\n     [authors=Steven Bird | published=1997-07-22 | primary_category=cs.CL | id=cmp-lg/9707011]\n\n=== openreview (5 results) ===\n  1. State Space Models are Effective Sign Language Learners\n     https://openreview.net/forum?id=cErM6ylfGU\n     [authors= | rank=1 | id=cErM6ylfGU]\n  2. This is a well-executed paper with a principled motivation, honest reporting, and results that hold up to scrutiny on the primary benchmark. The phonological error analysis is genuinely novel. The main weaknesses are the unexplained mid-range underperformance, the lack of phonological supervision over the factorized subspaces, and the limited baseline comparisons on the new benchmark. These are significant but addressable.\n     https://openreview.net/forum?id=yC8ISHWNIh\n     [authors= | rank=2 | id=yC8ISHWNIh]\n  3. Speech vocoding for laboratory phonology\n     https://openreview.net/foru